# dev-toolbox MANIFEST
# format: id|type|path|entry|description
# type: git (alias fragment at git/<id>/alias.gitconfig) | shell (source file at shell/<id>/)
# entry: git alias name, or shell file name (informational)
# path: always points to the fragment/file inside the item's own git/<id>/ or shell/<id>/ dir
#
# add a new item: create the <type>/<id>/ dir (script.sh + alias.gitconfig/aliases.sh + README.md),
# add a line here.
chain|git|git/chain/alias.gitconfig|chain|Shows the branch chain (PR stack) from current to main
aliases|shell|shell/aliases/script.sh|aliases|Lists all shell and git aliases in a table, showing their source
update|shell|shell/update/script.sh|update|Updates system packages and installed dev tools (apt/brew/uv/poetry/mise/flatpak/snap/aqua/gcloud/rustup/pipx/cursor/vscode/sublime/podman/gh+extensions/docker desktop/mas), cross-platform Ubuntu+macOS via uname detection, plus apt autoremove/autoclean cleanup, skipping any not installed
kinfo|shell|shell/kinfo/script.sh|kinfo|Shows Kubernetes deployment details (namespace, env, version, last deployer+timestamp) for an app, with an fzf picker when the app name is omitted
fix-network|shell|shell/fix-network/script.sh|fix_network|Fixes network instability, cross-platform Ubuntu+macOS via uname detection: optionally disables IPv6 (nmcli/networksetup) and flushes DNS cache (resolvectl/dscacheutil), restarts NetworkManager and Netskope (stagentd) if present (Linux only)
